com.f2prateek.ln
Class DebugLn

java.lang.Object
  com.f2prateek.ln.DebugLn
All Implemented Interfaces:
LnInterface
public class DebugLn
extends Object
implements LnInterface

Implementation of LnInterface that prints to Log. This class will use your package name, source file, line number of the call as the tag and adds the current thread to the message. Override processTag(String) to modify this behaviour. You can also override processMessage(String). A good scenario to do this would be if you wanted to automatically filter sensitive information from your logs (credit card numbers, passwords, etc.). Subclass this if you want to have an easy to use implementation of managing log levels. You can override println(int, String) to change the endpoint (e.g. log to crash server and not android.util.Log} .

getLoggingLevel

public int getLoggingLevel()
Get the current logging level. Should return one of : 1. Log.VERBOSE 2. Log.ERROR 3. Log.INFO 4. Log.WARN 5. Log.ERROR 6. Log.ASSERT 7. -1 if not supported

processMessage

protected String processMessage(String msg)
Provide a message for logging. This prepends the current thread to the message. Override this if you want to filter sensitive information, or add extra information to each message before dispatching.

Parameters:
msg - The message evaluated from the format, arguments and exceptions.
Returns:
The message that is logged

processTag

protected String processTag(String packageName)
Provide a tag for logging. By default this returns a tag with the package name, file name, and line number of the calling function. Override this to show different information in the tag.

Parameters:
packageName - the packageName of the app
Returns:
the tag to log with
